com.gsma.mobileconnect.r2.cache
Interface ICache

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractCache, ConcurrentCache
public interface ICache

Interface for the cache used during the discovery process, cache is mainly used to cache DiscoveryResponse objects but can also be used to cache any data used during the Discovery process.

Since:
2.0

<T extends AbstractCacheable> T get(java.lang.String key,
                                    java.lang.Class<T> clazz)
                                throws CacheAccessException
Return a cached value based on the key. If it is found to be setExpired it will be removed from the cache.

Equivalent to calling: 

     cache.get(key, true);

Type Parameters:
T - the type to be returned from the cache.
Parameters:
key - to match (required).

Type Parameters:
